title: Emergency personnel respond after a vehicle crashed - WKYC-TV Cleveland
text:
State parade Three people killed by a car that crashed into a crowd at the parade route during Homecoming Check out this story on WKYC.com: http://usat.ly/1S2Nz00 Emergency personnel respond after a vehicle crashed into a crowd of spectators during the Oklahoma State University homecoming parade in Stillwater, Okla. The driver, Adacia Chambers, 25, was arrested and jailed on suspicion of driving under the influence, Stillwater Police Capt.
 WKYC-TV Cleveland.
